def merge_sorted_lists(list1_x, list2_x):
    result_x = []
    i, j = 0, 0

    while i < len(list1_x) and j < len(list2_x):
        if list1_x[i] < list2_x[j]:
            result_x.append(list1_x[i])
            i += 1
        else:
            result_x.append(list2_x[j])
            j += 1

    result_x.extend(list1_x[i:])
    result_x.extend(list2_x[j:])

    return result_x
